<h2>Return Journey: Dotonbori to OMO Hotel</h2>

<p>The return journey is equally straightforward—simply reverse the route:</p>

<ol>
<li>Walk 5-8 minutes from Dotonbori back to Namba Station</li>
<li>Purchase your ticket to "Kansai Airport" (same options: Rapi:t ¥1,490 or Airport Express ¥970)</li>
<li>Board the train toward Kansai Airport</li>
<li>Exit at Kansai Airport Station (terminal station—everyone gets off)</li>
<li>Follow signs to Aeroplaza/Hotel (5-7 minute walk back to your hotel)</li>
</ol>

<h2>Alternative: Airport Limousine Bus</h2>

<p>If you prefer buses or are traveling late at night when trains are less frequent:</p>

<div class="highlight">
<strong>Limousine Bus Option</strong><br>
• <strong>Departure:</strong> Kansai Airport Terminal 1, Bus Stop 8<br>
• <strong>Arrival:</strong> Namba OCAT or Dotonbori area<br>
• <strong>Journey time:</strong> 50-65 minutes (traffic dependent)<br>
• <strong>Cost:</strong> ¥1,100<br>
• <strong>Frequency:</strong> Every 20 minutes during daytime<br>
• <strong>Note:</strong> Can be slower during rush hour traffic
</div>

<h2>Navigating Dotonbori: What to Expect</h2>

<p>Once you arrive in Dotonbori, you'll immediately recognize the area by its iconic illuminated signs including the famous Glico Running Man, giant moving crab, and other neon advertisements. The main entertainment strip runs along both sides of the Dotonbori Canal.</p>

<p><strong>Key landmarks to orient yourself:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ebisubashi Bridge:</strong> The central bridge with the Glico sign photo spot</li>
<li><strong>Dotonbori Canal:</strong> Runs east-west through the district</li>
<li><strong>Shinsaibashi:</strong> Covered shopping arcade one block north of the canal</li>
<li><strong>Hozenji Yokocho:</strong> Traditional alley with stone-paved streets</li>
</ul>

<h2>Pro Tips for First-Time Visitors</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>Buy tickets early:</strong> Purchase your return ticket when you first arrive at Namba if traveling during evening rush hour (5-7 PM) to avoid crowds at machines</li>
<li><strong>IC card recommended:</strong> Consider getting an ICOCA card at Kansai Airport for easy transit throughout Osaka (can be purchased at ticket machines)</li>
<li><strong>Last trains:</strong> The last Rapi:t from Namba to the airport departs around 11:30 PM; Airport Express runs slightly later</li>
<li><strong>Luggage:</strong> Both train options have overhead racks and space near doors for luggage; Rapi:t has more dedicated luggage space</li>
<li><strong>Save on navigation:</strong> Download the Google Maps app and enable offline maps for Osaka before your trip</li>
<li><strong>Peak times:</strong> Avoid traveling during morning rush hour (7:30-9 AM) and evening rush hour (5-7 PM) if possible, especially on weekdays</li>
</ul>

